# Skillfold - AI Pipeline Compiler

Skillfold is a configuration language and compiler for multi-agent AI pipelines.
It compiles YAML config into platform-specific agent skill files.

## Project Structure

- `skillfold.yaml` - Pipeline configuration (resources, skills, state, team)
- `skills/` - Atomic skill definitions (each has a SKILL.md)
- `build/` - Compiled output (default --out-dir)
- `skillfold.schema.json` - JSON Schema for IDE autocompletion

## Config Structure

Four top-level sections in skillfold.yaml:

```yaml
resources:   # Resource namespace declarations for state location validation
skills:
  atomic:    # Path references to skill directories containing SKILL.md
  composed:  # Composition declarations combining atomic skills into agents
state:       # Typed state schema (primitives, lists, custom types, locations)
team:
  orchestrator: # Optional skill to append generated execution plan
  flow:         # Directed execution graph with routing, loops, parallel map
```

## Key Commands

```bash
npx skillfold                        # Compile pipeline
npx skillfold --target cursor        # Compile to Cursor rules
npx skillfold --target claude-code   # Compile to Claude Code agents
npx skillfold validate               # Validate config without compiling
npx skillfold watch                  # Auto-recompile on changes
npx skillfold run --target claude-code  # Execute the pipeline
npx skillfold list                   # Inspect pipeline structure
npx skillfold graph --html           # Interactive pipeline visualization
npx skillfold search [query]         # Search npm for shared skills
npx skillfold init                   # Scaffold a new pipeline
```

## Skill Authoring

Each atomic skill lives in its own directory with a SKILL.md file:

```markdown
---
name: skill-name
---

# Skill Name

Instructions for the agent when this skill is active.
Keep skills focused on a single responsibility.
```

## Composition

Composed skills combine atomic skills by reference:

```yaml
skills:
  composed:
    my-agent:
      skills: [planning, code-writing, testing]
```

The compiler concatenates skill bodies in declared order.

## TypeScript Conventions

- Strict mode, ESM modules
- Node stdlib imports use `node:` prefix
- File extensions in imports: `.js` (NodeNext module resolution)
- No `any`, no unnecessary type assertions
- Custom errors extend Error with descriptive messages

## State Schema

State fields have types, optional locations, and are validated at compile time:

```yaml
state:
  types:
    ReviewResult:
      approved: boolean
      comments: string
  fields:
    plan: string
    reviews:
      type: list<ReviewResult>
      location: github-issues
```

## Team Flow

Flow defines agent execution order with conditionals and parallel patterns:

```yaml
team:
  flow:
    planner:
      skill: planning-agent
      next: engineer
    engineer:
      skill: dev-agent
      next: reviewer
    reviewer:
      skill: review-agent
      next:
        - when: reviews[-1].approved == true
          then: done
        - default: engineer
```
